{{Politics of Burundi}}
A '''referendum on the Charter of National Unity''' was held in [[Burundi]] on 9 February 1991. The charter would abolish ethnic discrimination and give a mandate for the government to write a new constitution. It was approved by 89.77% of voters with a 96% turnout.<ref>[http://africanelections.tripod.com/bi.html#1991_Referendum Elections in Burundi] African Elections Database</ref> Following the Charter's approval, work began on the drafting of a new constitution which was approved in a [[Burundi constitutional referendum, 1992|referendum]] held on 9 March 1992. It was promulgated on 13 March 1992.
