'''VADS''' (formerly an initialism for '''Visual Arts Data Service'''<ref>{{cite web | url=http://education.guardian.co.uk/higher/links/arts/0,,472417,00.html | title=More higher education news : Education Higher Links Front : Arts | publisher=[[The Guardian]] |accessdate=25 April 2008}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.artdes.mmu.ac.uk/visualresources/designcouncil/ | title=Design Council Slide Collection | publisher=[[Manchester School of Art]] | quote=As a result of these projects, over 13,000 images have been made available online via the website of the Visual Arts Data Service (VADS).|accessdate=31 May 2014}}</ref>) is a UK organisation that provides digital images and other visual arts resources free and copyright cleared for use in UK [[higher education]] and [[further education]].  It has provided services to the academic community since 3 March 1997,<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.ahds.ac.uk/visualarts/about/reports/pr_97-98.htm | title=VADS annual report 1997–1998 | publisher=[[Arts and Humanities Data Service]] | quote=The Visual Arts Data Service was officially launched on 3rd March 1997 when the full-time VADS officer began in post.|accessdate=31 May 2014}}</ref> and has built up a portfolio of visual art collections comprising over 100,000 images.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.intute.ac.uk/blog/2008/04/25/vads-re-launch-free-copyright-cleared-images-for-academic-use/ | title=VADS re-launch: free copyright-cleared images for academic use |first=Mary |last=Burslem|date=25 April 2008| publisher=[[Intute]] | accessdate=25 April 2008}}</ref>  VADS is based at the [[University for the Creative Arts]] at Farnham.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.vads.ac.uk/about/ | title=About | publisher=VADS |accessdate=31 May 2014}}</ref>

